We have had in place a method for generating unique identifiers for each of our quarterly publications. We are planning to use a functional relationship to map our identifiers to unique DOIs. If we were required to accept EZID created ids, we would then need to maintain a look-up table whose sole purpose was to map our unique identifiers to a new set of arbitrary unique identifiers. This would add significant overhead and development expense to fit into our workflow.

In the first year, we plan to create DOIs for all of our quarterly publications going back to Fall 1997 and then to generate DOIs for our new publications on a quarterly basis. In future years, we would need only to create DOIs for that year’s publications.
